** diluting an acid:
here mixing concentrated acid with water is known as diluting an acid:
acid+ water is highly exothermic

here when you add water to acid then it will produce a lot of heat and cause burn and many things :
so always add acid to water slowly:


acid and alkalis they both consist of ions so they so they generate the current and so on:
 where as gloucose: C6H12O6 alcohol C2H5OH they dont contain ions so they do not carry current or charge:

