| **Name**                | **Common Name**      | **Chemical Formula** | **Use / Remark**                                                |
| ----------------------- | -------------------- | -------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Sodium Hydroxide**    | **Caustic Soda**     | **NaOH**             | Used in soap making, paper industry, and as a cleaning agent    |
| **Calcium Oxychloride** | **Bleaching Powder** | **CaOCl₂**           | Used for bleaching clothes and disinfecting water               |
| **Sodium Bicarbonate**  | **Baking Soda**      | **NaHCO₃**           | Used in baking, as an antacid, and for cleaning                 |
| **Sodium Carbonate**    | **Washing Soda**     | **Na₂CO₃·10H₂O**     | Used in washing clothes, softening hard water, and glass making |


** chlor alkali process:
In this process, aqueous sodium chloride (brine) is electrolyzed to produce sodium hydroxide, chlorine gas, and hydrogen gas.

NACL + H20 = NAOH + CL2 +H2
AT ELECTRODES:
| **Electrode**   | **Reaction**                             | **Product**                                        |
| --------------- | ---------------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------- |
| **Anode (+)**   | ( 2Cl^- \rightarrow Cl_2 + 2e^- )        | Chlorine gas (**Cl₂**)                             |
| **Cathode (–)** | ( 2H_2O + 2e^- \rightarrow H_2 + 2OH^- ) | Hydrogen gas (**H₂**) and Hydroxide ions (**OH⁻**) |

** PRODUCT FORMED:
 CHLORINE GAS: AT ANODE:
 HYDROGEN GAS AT CATHODE:
 SODIUM HYDROXIDE IN SOLUTION:

** BLEACHING POWDER REACTION:
CAOH2 + CL2 = CAOCL2 + H20

** BAKING SODA:

H2O+ CO2+ NH3 = NH4CL + NAHCO3:

 ** BAJING SODA:
NaCl+H2​O+CO2​+NH3​→NaHCO3​+NH4​Cl

** WASHING SODA:
Na2​CO3​+10H2​O→Na2​CO3​⋅10H2​O

IMPORTANT CHEMICAL FORMULA:
| **Name**            | **Formula**  | **Type**                   |
| ------------------- | ------------ | -------------------------- |
| Hydrochloric acid   | HCl          | Acid                       |
| Sulphuric acid      | H₂SO₄        | Acid                       |
| Nitric acid         | HNO₃         | Acid                       |
| Acetic acid         | CH₃COOH      | Weak acid                  |
| Carbonic acid       | H₂CO₃        | Weak acid                  |
| Sodium hydroxide    | NaOH         | Base                       |
| Potassium hydroxide | KOH          | Base                       |
| Calcium hydroxide   | Ca(OH)₂      | Base                       |
| Ammonium hydroxide  | NH₄OH        | Weak base                  |
| Magnesium hydroxide | Mg(OH)₂      | Weak base                  |
| Sodium chloride     | NaCl         | Salt                       |
| Sodium carbonate    | Na₂CO₃·10H₂O | Washing soda               |
| Sodium bicarbonate  | NaHCO₃       | Baking soda                |
| Calcium oxychloride | CaOCl₂       | Bleaching powder           |
| Calcium carbonate   | CaCO₃        | Limestone / Chalk / Marble |
| Ammonium chloride   | NH₄Cl        | Salt                       |
| Sodium sulphate     | Na₂SO₄       | Salt                       |
| Copper sulphate     | CuSO₄·5H₂O   | Blue vitriol               |
| Zinc sulphate       | ZnSO₄        | White vitriol              |


| **No.** | **Reaction Type**                                  | **Chemical Equation**                    | **Products / Notes**   |
| ------- | -------------------------------------------------- | ---------------------------------------- | ---------------------- |
| **1**   | **Acid + Base (Neutralization)**                   | HCl + NaOH → NaCl + H₂O                  | Salt + Water           |
| **2**   | **Acid + Metal**                                   | Zn + 2HCl → ZnCl₂ + H₂↑                  | Hydrogen gas released  |
| **3**   | **Acid + Metal Carbonate**                         | Na₂CO₃ + 2HCl → 2NaCl + H₂O + CO₂↑       | Carbon dioxide gas     |
| **4**   | **Acid + Metal Hydrogen Carbonate**                | NaHCO₃ + HCl → NaCl + H₂O + CO₂↑         | CO₂ causes fizz        |
| **5**   | **Base + Non-metallic Oxide**                      | 2NaOH + CO₂ → Na₂CO₃ + H₂O               | Salt + Water           |
| **6**   | **Metal Oxide + Acid**                             | CuO + 2HCl → CuCl₂ + H₂O                 | Salt + Water           |
| **7**   | **Lime Water Test**                                | Ca(OH)₂ + CO₂ → CaCO₃ + H₂O              | Turns milky            |
| **8**   | **Excess CO₂ Reaction**                            | CaCO₃ + CO₂ + H₂O → Ca(HCO₃)₂            | Milkiness disappears   |
| **9**   | **Thermal Decomposition (Limestone)**              | CaCO₃ → CaO + CO₂                        | Quick lime formation   |
| **10**  | **Thermal Decomposition (Baking Soda)**            | 2NaHCO₃ → Na₂CO₃ + H₂O + CO₂             | Used in baking         |
| **11**  | **Formation of Washing Soda**                      | Na₂CO₃ + 10H₂O → Na₂CO₃·10H₂O            | Crystallization        |
| **12**  | **Formation of Bleaching Powder**                  | Ca(OH)₂ + Cl₂ → CaOCl₂ + H₂O             | Disinfectant           |
| **13**  | **Chlor-Alkali Process**                           | 2NaCl + 2H₂O → 2NaOH + H₂ + Cl₂          | Electrolysis of brine  |
| **14**  | **Formation of Baking Soda (Solvay Process)**      | NaCl + H₂O + CO₂ + NH₃ → NaHCO₃ + NH₄Cl  | Used in cooking        |
| **15**  | **Reaction of Sodium Carbonate with Acid**         | Na₂CO₃ + 2HCl → 2NaCl + CO₂ + H₂O        | Gas evolution          |
| **16**  | **Reaction of Ammonium Hydroxide with Acid**       | NH₄OH + HCl → NH₄Cl + H₂O                | Neutralization         |
| **17**  | **Reaction of Strong Base with Weak Acid**         | NaOH + CH₃COOH → CH₃COONa + H₂O          | Salt of weak acid      |
| **18**  | **Reaction of Metal with Base (Amphoteric Metal)** | 2Al + 2NaOH + 6H₂O → 2Na[Al(OH)₄] + 3H₂↑ | Hydrogen gas formed    |
| **19**  | **Quick Lime + Water**                             | CaO + H₂O → Ca(OH)₂                      | Slaked lime            |
| **20**  | **Slaked Lime + CO₂**                              | Ca(OH)₂ + CO₂ → CaCO₃ + H₂O              | Lime water turns milky |


| **Substance** | **Chemical Formula**         | **Common Name / Product**  |
| ------------- | ---------------------------- | -------------------------- |
| NaOH          | Sodium Hydroxide             | Caustic soda               |
| NaHCO₃        | Sodium Bicarbonate           | Baking soda                |
| Na₂CO₃·10H₂O  | Sodium Carbonate Decahydrate | Washing soda               |
| CaOCl₂        | Calcium Oxychloride          | Bleaching powder           |
| Ca(OH)₂       | Calcium Hydroxide            | Slaked lime                |
| CaCO₃         | Calcium Carbonate            | Limestone / Chalk / Marble |



